description.narrative: In 2021, despite major constraints and a more challenging context than the previous year, UNICEF continued to support access to education through first grade enrolment and non-formal education opportunities. 5,259 six year olds and out of school overaged children were enrolled in first grate in the 106 schools supported by UNICEF as well as through the Non-Formal Education initiative including 1100 who were displaced due to armed-gangs’ activities and school closures in their areas.; UNICEF also continued to support preschool activities for more than 2,300 children in the North through the Haiti Wins program. | Status:Met | As-of Date:17/01/2022
